        <Parent_String>zitherlike chordophones: plucked [300224198], zitherlike chordophones [300224193], chordophones [300041641], sound devices by acoustical characteristics [300041621], sound devices (equipment) [300387677], Sound Devices (hierarchy name) [300041619], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Zitherlike chordophones of northern and western Uganda, having a shallow trough-shaped resonator with two long straight sides and two shorter curved sides, bearing a single string laced up and down from end to end through holes or over notches.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000030041/Sadie, New Grove Dictionary of Musical Instruments (1984)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000026541/Marcuse, Musical Instruments Dictionary (1975)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cordófonos tipo cítara del norte y occidente de Uganda consistentes en un resonador poco profundo en forma de artesa con dos lados largos rectos y dos lados más cortos curvos, y que tienen una sola cuerda amarrada arriba y abajo de un extremo a otro a través de orificios o sobre muescas. Arpas arqueadas del pueblo Ganda, de Uganda, con cuerpo circular u oval y ocho cuerdas</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Citerachtige chordofonen uit het noorden en westen van Oeganda, met een ondiepe trogvormige klankbodem met twee lange, rechte en twee kortere, kromme zijden, waarop één enkele snaar wordt gedragen die door gaten of over inkepingen heen, op en neer van de ene naar de andere kant van het instrument is geregen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052488/Etnomusicologisch Centrum</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指烏干達北部和西部的弦鳴樂器，類似齊特琴。恩南嘉琴具有淺槽狀共鳴箱，共鳴箱其中兩個側邊長而直，另外兩個側邊較短且彎，單弦的兩端通過凹洞或刻痕緊緊繫起。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Zitherinstrument aus Norduganda und Westuganda mit einem flachen, trogförmigen Resonator, der zwei lange gerade Seiten und zwei kürzere geschwungene Seiten hat und eine einzige Saite trägt, die von Ende zu Ende hin und her durch Löcher oder über Kerben gespannt ist.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
